==English==

{{rank|time|only|like|76|little|now|then|A}}

===Etymology===
Old English [[lytel|lȳtel]], from West Germanic ''*lutila-''.  Cognate with Dutch [[luttel]], dialectal German [[lützel]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/'lɪtəl/}}, /lɪəl/
*{{audio|en-us-little.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪtəl|-ɪtəl]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|'''[[less]]''', '''[[lesser]]''' or '''[[littler]]'''|'''[[least]]''' or '''[[littlest]]'''}}

# [[small]]
#:''This is a '''little''' table.''
# {{italbrac|of a sibling}} younger
#:''This is my '''little''' brother.''
# trifling, negligable
#:''It's of '''little''' importance.''

====Antonyms====
*[[large]], [[big]]

====Usage notes====
*In cases where ''[[few]]'' would be used with countable nouns, ''little'' should be used with uncountable nouns.

